Author : Sabyasachi Upadhyay
	

The app1.py python script uses tweepy to connect to the twitter api to fetch the data from twitter. For example, for movie "RideAlong", the app1.py reads the moviename from movies_app1 and fetches the corresponding tweets of the last seven days from the site, and writes them onto a file RideALong with each line containig
parameters delimited by ~~~.

stemming.py or stemming1.py contains the Multinomial Naive Bayesian Classifier to classify the tweets.

The training data is in worldwarz file, containing positive tweets(rt-polarity.pos) and the negative tweets(rt-polarity.neg)

 
